        "title": "Could not load the following font on WebSphere",
        "body": "<p>Getting the following error while trying to export to a PDF using <em>JasperReports<\/em>.<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Error when the error message is being printed is as follows:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<p>Could not load the following font :<\/p>\n\n<p>pdfFontName   : Arial.ttf<\/p>\n\n<p>pdfEncoding   : Identity-H<\/p>\n\n<p>isPdfEmbedded : true]<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>My JRXML<\/strong>\n<code>&lt;textElement&gt;\n&lt;font pdfFontName=\"Arial.ttf\" isPdfEmbedded =\"true\" pdfEncoding =\"Identity-H\"/&gt;\n&lt;/textElement&gt;<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Using:<\/strong>\nWebSphere Application Server version 7<br/>\n<em>JasperReports<\/em> version 3 jar<\/p>\n\n<p>The Arial.ttf font file is present in the .../web-inf/classes and the default location of fonts in a unix machine.<\/p>\n\n<p>I have almost no knowledge in <em>JasperReports<\/em> and need to debug this issue. Kindly help me with the things I might be missing/overlooked or of more specific information is required about any part.<\/p>\n",
